title: Hundreds of vikings arrive in Shetland for Up Helly Aa
text: Here come the marauders! Scores of axe-wielding vikings in winged helmets gather for fiery festival 'invasion' of the Shetland Islands Around 1,000 Vikings descended on Lerwick, Shetland, for the 2017 Up Helly Aa annual Scandinavian festival Despite their impressive costumes and dedication in the freezing cold, the food looked less than authentic The torch-lit procession, with thousands of people taking part, is led by the Guizer Jarl, known as chief guizer Every year it ends with the burning of a galley, an authentic longship, and celebrations throughout the night Published: 13:25 GMT, 31 January 2017 | Updated: 00:04 GMT, 1 February 2017 68 shares
